# Prefer Built-in Tools Over Shell Commands

Always use the agent's built-in tools instead of shelling out to terminal commands:

| Task | Use This | NOT This |
|------|----------|----------|
| Search file contents | **Grep** tool | `grep` in Shell |
| Find files by name | **Glob** tool | `find`, `fd`, `ls -R` in Shell |
| Read file contents | **Read** tool | `cat`, `head`, `tail`, `less` in Shell |
| Edit files | **StrReplace** tool | `sed`, `awk`, `perl -i` in Shell |

Reserve the **Shell** tool for actual system operations: `git`, `dotnet build`, `npm`, running scripts, etc.

## FORBIDDEN: `rg` (ripgrep)

**`rg` is NOT installed on this system and MUST NEVER be invoked via Shell.** Any Shell call containing `rg ` will fail. This applies to all agents including subagents.

- To search file contents by pattern → use the **Grep** tool.
- To search for files by name → use the **Glob** tool.
- To search by meaning → use the **SemanticSearch** tool.

There is no exception. Do not attempt to install `rg`. Do not fall back to `grep` in Shell either — use the built-in **Grep** tool.
